k%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMassachusetts%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20announcement%2C%20Lyft%20said%20it%20hopes%20to%20be%20more%20transparent%20about%20how%20much%20drivers%20tend%20to%20earn%2C%20which%20could%20better%20prepare%20people%20deciding%20whether%20to%20drive%20for%20Lyft%20and%20how%20many%20hours%20to%20devote.%20Lyft%20noted%20in%20a%20separate%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lyft.com%2Fblog%2Fposts%2Fdriver-net-earnings%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhite%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%202023%2C%20the%20median%20US%20driver%20who%20used%20a%20personal%20vehicle%20earned%20%2430.68%20gross%20per%20hour%20of%20engaged%20time%2C%20meaning%20when%20driving%20to%20a%20rider%20and%20dropping%20them%20off.%20This%20value%20includes%20tips%20and%20bonuses%2C%20and%20Lyft%20said%20it%20has%20grown%2018%25%20since%20the%20second%20half%20of%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELyft%20calculated%20the%20total%20marginal%20cost%20per%20mile%20at%20%240.31%2C%20accounting%20for%20fuel%20costs%2C%20maintenance%20and%20repair%2C%20marginal%20depreciation%2C%20and%20cleaning.%20As%20calculated%20by%20Lyft%2C%20the%20median%20marginal%20cost%20per%20hour%20comes%20out%20to%20%247.02%2C%20bringing%20earnings%20down%20to%20%2423.46%20per%20engaged%20hour%20after%20expenses%2C%20factoring%20in%20tips%20and%20bonuses.%20Still%2C%2094%25%20of%20Lyft%20drivers%20only%20drive%20less%20than%2020%20hours%20a%20week%20and%20use%20driving%20to%20supplement%20other%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20released%20last%20October%20with%20Kara%20Swisher%2C%20Uber%20CEO%20Dara%20Khosrowshahi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpodcasts.apple.com%2Fus%2Fpodcast%2Fubers-profit-power-and-problems-with-ceo-dara-k%2Fid1643307527%3Fi%3D1000633061170%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esaid%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20company's%20take%20rate%20%E2%80%94%20the%20amount%20of%20passenger%20fares%20the%20company%20keeps%20%E2%80%94%2