onnel%20to%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20attacks%20against%20Israel%20on%20October%207%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUNRWA%20has%20more%20than%2013%2C000%20staff%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20panel%20was%20set%20up%20in%20consultation%20with%20UNRWA%20Commissioner-General%20Philippe%20Lazzarini%20and%20will%20be%20led%20by%20former%20French%20foreign%20minister%20Catherine%20Colonna%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.un.org%2Fen%2Fstory%2F2024%2F02%2F1146207%5C%22%3EUN%20News%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20will%20begin%20working%20from%20February%2014%20and%20an%20interim%20report%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20submitted%20to%20Guterres%20in%20late%20March.%20The%20final%20report%2C%20which%20will%20be%20made%20public%2C%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20completed%20by%20late%20April%2C%20according%20to%20UN%20News.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UN%20Office%20of%20Internal%20Oversight%20Services%20is%20already%20probing%20the%20allegations%20that%2012%20UNRWA%20personnel%20were%20involved%20in%20the%20October%207%20attack%2C%20and%20the%20independent%20panel%E2%80%99s%20probe%20will%20in%20parallel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Israel%20accused%20UNRWA%20staff%20of%20being%20involved%20with%20Hamas%2C%20nine%20Western%20countries%20withdrew%20their%20funding%20for%20the%20agency.%20Given%20the%20scale%20of%20destruction%20in%20Gaza%20due%20to%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20ongoing%20attacks%20which%20it%20claims%20are%20%E2%80%98retaliation%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20and%20which%20the%20International%20Court%20of%20Justice%20is%20probing%20on%20grounds%20of%20%E2%80%98genocide%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20UNRWA%E2%80%99s%20relief%20work%20has%20been%20viewed%20as%20providing%20essential%20humanitarian%20relief.%20Lazzarini%20had%20said%20this%20funding%20suspension%20is%20%E2%80%9Cshocking%E2%80%9D%20as%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20lives%20of%20people%20in%20Gaza%20depends%20on%20this%20support%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.channel4.com%2Fnews%2Fisraels-evidence-of-u