20over%201%20million%20followers%20today%2C%20Dhiraj%20has%20risen%20out%20of%20obscurity%20through%20his%20creativity%2C%20passion%20and%20desire%20to%20improve%20his%20communication%20skills%20by%20teaching%20others%20how%20to%20talk%20like%20a%20native%20English%20speaker%20despite%20lacking%20the%20resources%20that%20most%20content%20creators%20possess.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20spoke%20to%20Dhiraj%20to%20dig%20a%20little%20deeper%20into%20his%20magical%20journey%20on%20the%20internet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-instgrm-captioned%20data-instgrm-version%3D%5C%2214%5C%22%20data-instgrm-permalink%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC2TyPKJABP-%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26amp%3Butm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC2TyPKJABP-%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3EView%20this%20post%20on%20Instagram%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Freel%2FC2TyPKJABP-%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20post%20shared%20by%20Dhiraj%20Takri%20(%40dhirajtakri)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ELockdown%20opportunity%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20studying%20at%20a%20local%20village%20school%20till%20matriculation%20(Class%2010)%2C%20Dhiraj%20went%20to%20a%20nearby%20town%20to%20complete%20his%20intermediate%20(high%20school)%20but%20failed%20his%20Class%2012%20examinations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CThings%20at%20home%20weren%E2%80%99t%20easy%20because%20our%20financial%20situation%20was%20unstable.%20My%20father%20used%20to%20repair%20bicycles%20while%20my%20mother%20travelled%20from%20one%20village%20to%20another%20selling%20bangles%20and%20other%20kinds%20of%20jewellery.%20After%20taking%20my%20Class%2012%20exams%2C%20I%20went%20to%20Kerala%20for%20a%20year%20where%20I%20lived%20and%20studied%20at%20a%20Christian%20theological%20training%20institute%20in%20Thiruvalla%2C%20Kerala.%20The%20only%20requirement%20to%20study%20there%20was%20a%20matriculation%20certificate.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresently%2C%20his%20parents%20are%20unemployed%20but%20his%20elder%20brother%20runs%20a%20local%20Jan%20Seva%20Kendra%20(common%20services%20centre).%20These%20centres%20assist%20residents%20access%20essential%20services%20online%20such%20as%20Aadahaar%20and%20PAN%20card%20services%2C%20payment%20of%20household%20bills%2C%20etc.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20it%20was%20a%20two-year%20course%2C%20he%20only%20studied%20there%20for%20a%20year%20because%20of%20the%20national%20lockdown%20imposed%20following%20COVID-19.%20It%20was%20at%20this%20institute%20where%20he%20started%20learning%20English.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20we%20weren%E2%80%99t%20allowed%20regular%20access%20to%20our%20mobile%20phones.%20Every%20Saturday%2C%20they%20would%20allow%20us%20to%20use%20our%20phones%20for%20three%20hours.%20Back%20then%2C%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20even%20have%20a%20smartphone.%20I%20had%20a%20Jio%20phone%20with%20basic%20features.%20During%20one%20such%20session%2C%